{
  "texts": [
    "The decision to focus on affinity towards PPAR sub-family members was made to align with their clinical significance 48.",
    "Applying these ranking criteria led to the identification of twice the top-5 molecules (1, 2, 6-13), depicted in Fig. 3b.",
    "While exhibiting sufficient structural and scaffold novelty, the generated molecules also possess a topology commonly observed in modulators of the PPAR subfamily, as captured by the three different QSAR models.",
    "Specifically, they feature an acidic head group connected to an aromatic core through a linker.",
    "Furthermore, this core is linked to another single-or bicyclic aromatic ring system."
  ]
}